  script_tag(name:"vuldetect", value:"Checks if a vulnerable package version is present on the target host.");

  script_tag(name:"insight", value:"A missing input sanitization in spamass-milter, a milter used to filter mail through spamassassin, was discovered. This allows a remote attacker to inject and execute arbitrary shell commands.

For the stable distribution (lenny), this problem has been fixed in version 0.3.1-8+lenny1.

For the testing (squeeze) and unstable (sid) distribution this problem has been fixed in version 0.3.1-9.

We recommend that you upgrade your spamass-milter package.");

  script_tag(name:"affected", value:"'spamass-milter' package(s) on Debian 5.");

  script_tag(name:"solution", value:"Please install the updated package(s).");

